It&#39;s a warning meaning that you could group several OneToOne declarations into a single one (see [JDL syntax][1])

    relationship OneToOne {
      JobHistory{department} to Department
    }

    relationship OneToOne {
      JobHistory{job} to Job
    }

could be rewritten as:

    relationship OneToOne {
      JobHistory{department} to Department
      JobHistory{job} to Job
    }

If you think that this message could be improved or that this warning is not useful, you should report it on https://github.com/jhipster/jhipster-ide


  [1]: https://www.jhipster.tech/jdl/#-relationship-declaration

